<i>Friday, Aug.</i> 11.                <i>MR. Belford acquaints his friend with the generosity of Lord M. and the Ladies of his family; and with the lady's grateful sentiments' upon the occasion.</i>                <i>He says, that in hopes to avoid the pain of seeing him, she intends to answer his letter of the 7th, tho' much against her inclination,</i>                 <i>Mr. Belford insists upon the promise he had made him, not to molest the lady: And gives him the contents of her answer to Lord M. and the Ladies, declining their generous offers,</i> See Letter CV. <i>p.</i> 348.